03/12/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer and EU security chief Javier Solana urged war crimes indictees Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic Thursday (2 December) to surrender to The Hague tribunal. 
The NATO and EU officials were in Sarajevo for the handover of the NATO peacekeeping mission to the new EU force. 
They stressed that the two former Bosnian Serb leaders could be certain of fair trials at The Hague.
In other news Thursday, chief UN war crimes prosecutor Carla del Ponte announced that the tribunal plans to hand down eight to ten more indictments this year. 
Prosecutors are completing their review of charges against former leaders of the Kosovo Liberation Army. 
(Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 03/12/04; FENA, B92 - 02/12/04)
